The paper deals with graph problems in the Massively Parallel Computations (MPC) model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a likely category. The main problem studied is maximal matching, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions approximation algorithms, which is a topic in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper mentions the congested clique model, which is a model for distributed computing, and therefore cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category.
